<li><font color="#e00000"><strong>SECURITY FIX: Several remote buffer overflows can occur in the SSL2 server and SSL3 client of the <a href="http://man.openbsd.org/?query=ssl&amp;sektion=8">ssl(8)</a> library, as in the ASN.1 parser code in the <a href="http://man.openbsd.org/?query=crypto&amp;sektion=3">crypto(3)</a> library, all of them being potentially remotely exploitable.</strong></font><br>
